This README file contains information on the contents of the
meta-kp layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.


Dependencies
============

This layer depends on:

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/bitbake
  branch: master

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core
  layers: meta
  branch: master

  URI: https://github.com/agherzan/meta-raspberrypi
  layers: meta
  branch: pyro


Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the meta-kp layer to your build
 II. Recipes


I. Adding the meta-kp layer to your build
=================================================

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the meta-kp layer exists at the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the meta-kp layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-poky \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-meta-kp \
    "


II. Recipes
========

recipes-example: example of a static library and relative application taken from the book Embedded Linux Projects Using Yocto Project Cookbook

rs-piface: first version of the pifacedigital library done without GIT and Makefiles

recipes-piface: version with GIT and Makefiles

To have the pifacedigital tool inside the final rpi-basic-image use
IMAGE_INSTALL_append = " \
    libpifacedigital \
"


